EXTRACTED VALUE: The audio soars even higher than the graphics.
It's not flawless, but it's worth the purchase. Until next year, this is as good as its going to get.
While it sure isn't a AAA game, it's hard to fault Dark Sector for anything past the seriously broken melee attack.
Even though it isn't a direct adaptation of a film, Stranglehold is probably the best example of a movie-based game to date.
If you are looking for originality, you'll find some here, but most of the game is a combination of several great aspects of other big name games.
Despite the game's problems, Battlefield 2: Modern Combat is still fun if you play online and don't need any real depth in your first person shooters.
